flowchart TD
    A[🇧🇷 Customer selects Pix] --> B{Pix Flow Type}

    B -->|QR Code / Copy-Paste| C[Merchant generates\nPix QR code via API]
    B -->|Pix by Proxy| D[Customer enters\nCPF, email, or phone]

    C --> E[Display QR code\nto customer]
    E --> F[Customer opens\nbanking app]
    F --> G[Scans QR code\nor pastes Pix code]

    D --> H[PSP resolves Pix key\nvia DICT directory]

    G --> I{Customer confirms\npayment in bank app}
    H --> I

    I -->|Approved| J[Instant settlement\nvia Central Bank SPI]
    I -->|Declined| K[❌ Payment failed]
    I -->|Timeout 30min| L[❌ QR code expired]

    J --> M[Central Bank settles\nin real-time 24/7/365]
    M --> N[Webhook notification\nto merchant]
    N --> O[✅ Payment confirmed\nwithin seconds]

    O --> P{Regulatory\nCompliance}
    P --> Q[CPF/CNPJ required\nfor all participants]
    P --> R[Central Bank\nPix regulation]
    P --> S[IOF tax on\nforeign transactions]
    P --> T[Anti-fraud: Pix\ntransaction limits]

    T --> U{Time-based Limits}
    U --> V[Daytime 6am–8pm:\nFull limit applies]
    U --> W[Nighttime 8pm–6am:\nR$1,000 default limit]

    R --> X{Merchant Requirements}
    X --> Y[Register Pix keys\nwith PSP]
    X --> Z[Implement webhook\nfor instant confirmation]
    X --> AA[Support refund via\nPix Devolução]

    style A fill:#4A90D9,color:#fff
    style O fill:#7ED321,color:#fff
    style K fill:#D0021B,color:#fff
    style L fill:#D0021B,color:#fff
    style R fill:#F5A623,color:#fff
    style T fill:#F5A623,color:#fff
